ve returned from\na two week vacation to Florida.\nThey report a grand vacation.\nMiss Patty Slagle entertained\nthe 4-H club at her home on\nMonday, July 29. During their\nmeeting they talked about plans\nfor the county fair.\nThere will be a hymn sing at\nthe church this Thursday eve\nning, Aug 8, begining at 8 o\u2019-,\nclock. Let\u2019s all come.\nMr. and Mrs. Tom Kelley of\nToledo and Mr. and Mrs. Nor\nris Highfield of Washington Cou\nrthouse, visited their ousin,\nMrs. Will Adams on Monday of\nlast week.\nMrs. Raymond Cole and son\nof Conneaut visited her sister\nand husband, Mr. and Mrs. El\nwin Evans and son Harry on\nSaturday and Sunday of last\nweek. Her mother Mrs. Cham-'\nplin who accompanied her re\nmained until Wednesday.\nMr. and Mrs. Joseph Antene\nand daughter, Laura, have re\nturned from a trip to De Rid\nler, La., where they visited their\nson in law and daughter S. I\nP. Wendall Thompson and wife.\nWendall is stationed at Fort\nPolk. On Sunday Mr. and Mrs.,\nAntene entertained relatives of'\n1\n1^\nH\u2019s possible with a fast recovery electric water heater\n1\nSpecial Low Rates\nIt\u2019s safe, clean and.completely automatic-nothing to light,\nnothing to \u201cgo out,\u201d nothing to attract curious youngsters.\nSB\nMr. and Mrs. Walden Smith\nof Iowa were calling on Mr. and\nMrs. H. B. Kile one day last\nweek. Mr. Smith is a grandson\nof the late Capt. H. P. Kile\nand a nephew of Mr. H. B. Kile.\nMr. and Mrs. E. H. Chace of\nWindsor were also calling at the\nKile home on Sunday, July 28.\nWANTED\nON STAGE\nActors\nActresses\nSet Designers\nProp Men\nScript Holders\nWardrobe Mistress\nMake Up Men\nand all resdents of Geauga\nCounty who are interested\nin \u201cLittle Theater\u201d work,\nat\nCHARDON AUDITORIUM\nMonday, August 5\nat 8 p.m.\nTO CAST 37 PARTS\nin\nTHE MAN WHO\nCAME TO DINNER\nGigantic Fall Production\nof\nTHE PIONEER\nPLAYERS\nOF GEAUGA COUNTY\nNewcomers to Geauga: We\nhave openngs for all. No\nexperience necessary.\nPlease atten